      • orderMoves

        public void orderMoves(java.util.ArrayList<Node> nodes,
              int depthleft)
        Takes a list of legal moves and attempts to sort them with the following weight:
      • 1. MVV-LVA (pxn before nxp)
      • 2. Killer Heuristic pvSearch prioritizes PV nodes as it finds them, and that always happens after this method is called, so PV nodes end up in the front of the arraylist.
Parameters:
nodes -
depthleft -

  • computePositionalScore

    public int computePositionalScore(boolean isWhite,
                         Node node)
    Computes the integer value of the position, taking into account piece mobility, king safety, mobility of the enemy, passed pawns, doubled pawns, pawn structure, etc. Very computationally expensive, will need to optimize this in the future.

  • computeMaterialScore

    public int computeMaterialScore()
    Computes the material score of a move. This is the difference between the amount of material (in points) for black and white. Positive means white is ahead in material.
